Interface WebSocketHttpResponse

All Superinterfaces:

All Known Implementing Classes:
DefaultWebSocketHttpResponse
public interface WebSocketHttpResponse extends io.netty.handler.codec.http.HttpResponse, Processor<io.netty.handler.codec.http.websocketx.WebSocketFrame, io.netty.handler.codec.http.websocketx.WebSocketFrame>
Combines HttpResponse and Processor into one message. So it represents a http response with a processor that can handle a WebSocket. This is only used for server side responses. For client side websocket requests, it's better to configure the reactive streams pipeline directly.
Author:
jroper, Graeme Rocher
